Vfx1ywSnvpI.description:
Shop Blogilates @ Target online: https://bit.ly/3rGJKZ0

Been driving around to a bunch of Targets all week and finally TODAY I just saw all my new Fall ‘22 designs in store for the 1st time!!

I am most excited for the more affordable gym bag! (The Blogilates one is only $49.99. Totally different fabric and design but the @POPFLEX By Blogilates one is $195) This took a lot of pitching and persuading to get @Target  to test my bag in some stores only…sooo it may be hard to find! I hope you guys like it because if it performs well, maybe I can design more for you at this price point and maybeeeee it can land at all stores so it’s easier for you to shop.

With the new fall ‘22 drop, I put an emphasis on making my designs more affordable for you guys. I am not saying Blogilates will be the cheapest of the cheap because I’ll never sacrifice quality, but I’ll try my hardest to find the best balance between design, quality, and price.

Other ✨new✨ things to look out for:

✔️ affordable yoga mat
✔️ affordable booty bands
✔️ foldable yoga mat - great for travel
✔️ improved gold weight rack
✔️ slider discs
✔️ gym flooring

Did you see any of these at your store yet!? Tell me if the gym bag is at your store or not! I’m so curious!

♥️Cassey

Ps: Everything is available at target.com too in case you can’t find it in store!
@Target

f0SHHP3rqYE.title: This is hands down the hardest thing about running your own business… #girlboss #entrepreneur
f0SHHP3rqYE.description:
Old Cassey was so broken that she couldn’t even dream up the team that I’m surrounded by today.

This week we had our 2nd annual Blogifam Retreat in San Diego and it was the first time I got to physically meet many of my team members face to face! We hired throughout the pandemic and all learned how to work remotely, so we never got a chance to spend time together in person. I think we were all nervous (even intimated) to meet one another!

But for the next 3 days, we laughed so hard our cheeks hurt and until tears ran down our faces. I felt so comfortable. I felt so…at home.

I can’t even properly express how full my heart feels right now. To finally be surrounded by the RIGHT people changes everything.

Just 3 years ago, I broke. I really was going to drop all of it.  @POPFLEX By Blogilates. Blogilates. All of it. The businesses were too painful to run. The toxicity was poisoning my mind, my body, my team, and my business. I wanted to throw it all away and just move far far away from LA.

I’m lucky Sam told me to just give it one last chance because if he didn’t say that, I really wouldn’t be here right now. I was completely broken. But when he said “just 30 more days” - I pulled together any last shreds of strength I had (which wasn’t much) and went into pure survival mode.

In those final days, something magical happened.

The universe put the right people in my path and helped me clear out the negativity so they I could breathe again…stand again…lead again.

My heart is filled with so much gratitude right now for every member of my team: the people who helped me find myself again. 

I was so lost, but now I am sure of it, I’m home.

♥️Cassey

8ulq19lvlBk.title: I sacrificed my foot for this vid 🥹 but, showing you this new hoodie design was a must. #fashion
8ulq19lvlBk.description:
Grab the hoodie: https://bit.ly/popflex-half-zip-hoodies-b

Operation: SAVE MY 🦶 

I am embarrassed how many times I drop my phone on my foot in a day. And each time I stand there and die in silence.

(Yes I sacrificed my foot for the footage in this video)

So in designing my half zip, I also wanted to zip up the pockets for foot safety ya know!?? Totally in love with how it turned out. When it comes to design, I love me some drama but not that much drama, balance is a must - a push and pull between masculinity and femininity is what strive for, and I obvi like to dial up the romance factor.

Oh and did you see what the bungee cords can do!?? It’s basically a 2 for 1 deal if you ask me 😁

The @POPFLEX By Blogilates  ⚡️Half Zip Warm Up Hoodie⚡️comes in XS to 3X and I’m wearing the small! I did not size up because it’s already oversized.

What do you think!?

♥️Cassey

Ps: Any questions? Suggestions? Just ask me in the comments!

j0j_VX6EP1o.title: You asked for the perf 🎒 so I designed the ✨Cora Backpack✨ Does it have everything u need? #fashion
j0j_VX6EP1o.description:
Grab the bag https://bit.ly/cora-backpack


No really. I was the kid at school with the double zipper Jansport backpack - 7 PERIODS OF TEXTBOOKS IN ALL COMPARTMENTS. Ya. My backpack extended out like 3 ft from my body because I refused to use the locker for efficiency purposes. 

I’m excited to share that the exact opposite of highschool me’s backpack is back in stock on @POPFLEX By Blogilates!  It’s the ✨Cora Backpack✨ yall!

She’s sleek and compact but holds A LOT.

✔️14 pockets 
✔️ waterproof neoprene shell
✔️ waterproof shoe compartment 
✔️ laptop pocket - holds my 13.5” MacBook with extra room 
✔️ 2 water bottle holders
✔️ key ring clip 
✔️ yoga mat holder 
✔️ fully lined
✔️cushy straps 

Ok. I think high school Cassey has been redeemed 🤓 BTW I tried to find high school pics of me and this backpack but they’re buried somewhere deep in my parents house states away. I feel like I need to go on a digitizing photos project! Those memories are so precious.

♥️ Cassey

Ps: I’m wearing the Twirl Dress in XS and Yoga mat is “Heart in the Clouds” from @POPFLEX By Blogilates  Shoes from Amazon!

AotKQ1_ttiQ.title: My fav type of ‘bag’ 🎒 #fashion #fashiondesigner #gym #pilates #entrepreneur #womenownedbusiness
AotKQ1_ttiQ.description:
Shop all gym bags: https://bit.ly/black-bag-restock

The first real thing I ever designed and sold was a bag. This was 13 years ago when I was in college, majoring in Biology but designing bags on the side. Back then I knew nothing. Like, zero. I thought bags had to have standard sizes regulated by some higher governing body or something. I had NO CLUE what I was doing, but you know what? I ended up figuring it out because when you want something really bad, you do whatever it takes to push through.

Today is an exciting day because my @POPFLEX By Blogilates  gym bags and backpacks are finalllyyyyyy back in stock! Thank you for being patient. These things just take a long time because everything sort of starts over when I decide to do a restock: fabric production, the sewing process, and shipping which is still affected by the Covid supply chain issues - yes, stilllll lingering now more than 2 years later!

Anyway, brought black back first because apparently that is everyone’s favorite color. I get it. It’s safe, it matches everything and it doesn’t get dirty.

Any questions on the bags? Ask away and I’ll answer in the comments!

♥️ Cassey

Ps: The video features the Belladonna Duffle and the Ella Duffle. Both have:

✔️ secret yoga mat holders
✔️ waterproof shoe compartment 
✔️ key ring clip
✔️ laptop holder - safely holds my 13.5” MacBook 
✔️ water bottle holders (fits a half gallon 64 Oz!)
✔️ made of waterproof neoprene fabric 
✔️ tons of extra pockets inside and outside 
✔️ fully lined 

You can get them now on https://www.popflexactive.com

orsgKOEh9js.title: I redesigned the 00’s yoga pant with a ‘22 flare... I hope it was worth the wait. #fashion
orsgKOEh9js.description:
Shop the Crisscross Flared Legging https://bit.ly/crisscross-hourglass-flare

Sorry it took so long!!!

Back in January when we released gen 1 of the @POPFLEX By Blogilates  flared legging (or yoga pants for us millennials and beyond 🥲) I didn’t expect them to sell out so fast! But instead of just remaking the same flares for you guys which would have taken about 3 months, I made the decision to redevelop this style again…which took nearly 9 months to arrive at gen 2.

Why? 

When it comes to serving you guys, there’s things that can bring you immediate gratification, but then there’s things that are temporarily frustrating but 100% worth waiting for. 

Look, I don’t believe in a life of not improving. Either for myself or my products. So here’s why you had to wait:

GEN 2 FLARED LEGGINGS

1. Added the crisscross waistband from our most viral legging to enhance your hourglass shape ✔️

2. Added POCKETSSSSSS but also made them super sleek and nearly invisible ✔️

3. Upgraded the fabric to ButterSmooth for a stretchier feel that is less prone to shrinkage! It fits like a hug and you can run in them without them falling down. They’re performance level flares.

Aaanndddd here’s what I kept from gen 1:

4. Anti-cameltoe front panel ✔️

5. 3 different lengths! 29”, 31”, 34”✔️

6. Squat proof✔️

7. Flares BELOW the knee to help lengthen your leg✔️

So, what do you think? Was it worth the wait?

♥️Cassey

Ps: I’m 5’5” wearing size small 31” inseam! You can get the @POPFLEX By Blogilates  ✨Crisscross Hourglass Flared Leggings✨ right now!

Zz3RBP-aq9c.title: I redesigned the classic crewneck and all I can say is… minor tweaks make a HUGE difference #fashion
Zz3RBP-aq9c.description:
Shop the Belle Sweater https://bit.ly/popflex-belle-sweater

I don’t know what it is, but over the past few years I’ve become totally enthralled by history. When I’m running on the treadmill, it’s no longer food shows I’m watching - it’s all historical non-fiction shows (I can’t do the made up stuff)!

I love learning the past because it tells me so much about the future. 

Anyway, I wanted to start off the video will a little history lesson on the invention of the first crewneck sweatshirt! It was invented by a football player named Benjamin Russell Jr. who also happens to be the son of THE founder of THE Russell Athletics brand! Benjamin created the initial crewneck sweater so he could wear something comfortable to football practice. How cool is it that 96 years later, the Russell brand is still strong and that design pretty much hasn’t changed? A true legacy brand and a true classic garment.

On the flip side though…96 years and the crewneck sweater hasn’t evolved to cater to women’s bodies besides just being smaller and being pink!?? Time to take the challenge!

I didn’t want to stray toooooo far from the classic 1926 crewneck, because it’s classic for a reason! It works! But does it excite me? No!! I wanted to update the crewneck sweater and give it a little bit more of a feminine flair. You know me and my romantic sleeves. So I did that 🙂

I hope you like the @POPFLEX By Blogilates ✨Belle Sweater✨

I love elevating basics because it’s such a challenge to balance the basic with the fashion. You can’t go too hard that it’s no longer basic…but you can’t go too soft that nothing happened.

Anyway tell me what you think!

♥️Cassey

Ps: I’m wearing small and this comes in XS - 3X in heather grey, black and sand! @POPFLEX By Blogilates at https://www.popflexactive.com

tLX3UcdxlPc.title: And I’m not even close to being done #fashion #designer #pilates #fitness
tLX3UcdxlPc.description:
When it comes to really difficult decisions, I cannot ignore my heart. What I’ve learned is that my heart knows where I belong and what I’m meant to do. Oftentimes, I find my happiness after venturing into the hardest of decisions and the stickiest of messes. The best rewards often come with the biggest challenges.

I can’t believe where I am today, and I’m not even close to where I want to be. And to be clear, I’m not not motivated by a dollar amount or the number or the number of followers. Unlike other companies who’s main goal is to sell or get investors, that’s not mine. My goal is to build a legacy brand with the best products that will live on after I die. My goal? Impact. I want grow and impact as many women as I can, while I can. To me, that’s the fun. That’s my motivation. You can ask Sam - I never look at the numbers. I’m purely excited by the creation process and then seeing you make my designs a part of your life. I LIVE for that. That is what fuels my 17 hour work days 7 days a week. Some may say I’m unhealthily addicted to my job but I don’t care what they say - what an absolute gift it is to be given the opportunity to have a career that aligns with my childhood dream, my passion and my mission. I feel lucky everyday.

This week I found out that @POPFLEX By Blogilates made the #INC5000 list 😳 We were named one of the fastest growing companies in North America. Apparently there are 33 million of them. 

And guess what? We’re just a tiny team. Made up of mostly women and Sam 🙂 I’m grateful for the opportunity to be surrounded with some of the kindest humans in the world: ideating, problem solving, and creating cool things every single day. From being days away from tossing out my brand and business a few years ago…to now this? Like I said, the most amazing things come after the toughest challenges.

I’ve still got a lot of work to do though - especially finding peace with my parents. It’s a difficult, emotional subject and there is a section of my heart that is still numb with pain. I’ll figure it out one day.

♥️Cassey

Shop the Pirouette Tiered Skort https://bit.ly/shop-pirouette-skort

Workout Skort…but make it ✨ROMANCE✨

Sometimes I like elevating a basic, but most of the time I’m just trying to live out my workout princess TSwift love story dreams.

I’m obsessed with fashion from earlier times because the silhouettes are so soft, feminine, and dreamy. What I truly enjoy is challenging myself and seeing if I can take a bit of the past and make it comfortable and functional enough for today’s active girl. Because if there’s one thing we know about women’s fashion throughout history - it had a tendency to restrict and limit mobility (think corsets) and comfort was not top of mind.

Anyway, here’s my latest @POPFLEX  creation! The 🩰Pirouette Skort🩰! 

I’m obsessed with how it turned out! Truly, the most romantic workout skort of my dreams…and now, of my reality. 

What do you think?

Ps: I’m wearing size small and I’m 5’5”. This skort is linked in my bio and ready for you at https://www.popflexactive.com 💕

6JcQNSbdsgg.title: I think I may have perfected this classic hoodie design for you… ☁️ #hoodie #fashion #designer
6JcQNSbdsgg.description:
Shop the Pullover Cloud Hoodie https://bit.ly/pullover-cloud-hoodie
__
Design challenge: elevate the classic hoodie.

Look, basics are basic for a reason. They are comfy and generally universally work on most people. But basic doesn’t have to mean uncute and unflattering. I took the classic hoodie (which was originally created in the 1930s by a male football player with men’s bodies in mind) and updated it with female bodies in mind - testing the shape and movement on my own body.

I’ve been working on this for a while now and I have been DYINGGGGG to share with you the final results! 

I’m so so so happy with the way the @POPFLEX Pullover Cloud Hoodie turned out! It’s soooo soft, voluptuous, and elevated looking.

🪡Bigger hood: yes to looking like a maiden running through an enchanted forest 
🪡Triangular bodice: gives you a baggy yet slimming shape
🪡Slightly lower neckline: less chokey and gives the illusion of a longer neck 
🪡Non-saggy hood due to the use of ☁️Cloud Fabric which is soooo soft and voluptuous…so instead, you get a lifted, regal collar effect even when the hood is down
🪡Blousey dropped sleeves to give the hoodie a romantic, feminine feeling 
🪡Swapped out basic drawstring hole stitches for metal hardware
🪡Swapped out sloppy knotted ends for a sleek endcap 

I mean, I can say all this…but you won’t truly understand te ✨magic✨ until you put it on! 

The hoodie comes in only 2 sizes: S/M and L/XL. But please don’t be fooled. L/XL can fit up to a 3X WITH ROOM. @POPFLEX  will be doing a try on video soon so you’ll see what I mean. This hoodie is SOOOOO fit flexible. I’m wearing the S/M and I’m normally a small. However, some of my friends who are normally larges like the fit of the S/M better than the L/XL. It’s kinda up to you and how baggy you want this! 

If you have any questions, ask me below! Hope you get to put this on your body soon!!

♥️Cassey 

Ps: The Pullover ☁️Cloud Hoodie is ready for you on Popflexactive.com in 7 colors…go!!!

This time, I decided to test this new gym bag in a print that made my heart happy! I’m obsessed with the crazy contrast between the peach florals and the neon lime!

r1LkE0ic9ss.title: This experience was seriously unreal #shorts #snorkeling #mexico #travel #travelvlog
r1LkE0ic9ss.description:
Sam and I went on a Minimoon for the past 10 days and it was truly an adventure - like, a little bit of the magical kind…but more of the shocking kind than I would have liked. Between all of the luscious guacamole and mesmerizing cenotes, there was us dodging swindlers and then getting swindled, and then almost dying in a minicar almost-accident - TWICE - just to name a few things 😅

Anyway, it was a memorable trip for sure and my favorite part besides getting time to focus on Sam and our relationship as husband and wife (not business partners) was getting over my fear of equalizing my ears. 

Over 10 years ago I did an introductory dive in the Great Barrier Reef with my sister and the tour guide did not properly explain how to equalize our ears so they ended up popping SHARPLY 🔪 and the pain was excruciating. Since then I’ve avoided diving because I’ve been terrified of that specific feeling. 

Anyway, on this trip, I asked our snorkeling guide if he could teach me how to do it and turns out, it’s way easier than I thought. You just hold your nose and blow as you go down. That’s it!!! The pressure relieves itself in a comforting way actually.

Finally, I was able to dive deeper and omg it was so freeing to explore. I felt like a mermaid! 🧜‍♀️ Next step, learn how to hold my breath longer.

Did we truly relax and did it feel like a Minimoon? Well, we tried. 🙃 But when you’re running a business, you’re never off and you know what, I choose this life and I wouldn’t trade it for anything. I love what I do and I don’t need a vacation from it - I just need dedicated time to not forget that there’s more to life than the biz and I need to experience as much of it as I can with Sam before we can’t anymore.

♥️Cassey

Ps: For those wondering, we were in Isla Mujeres and then Tulum (which was major vibes) and then Cozumel which is where all of this go pro footage is from. The tour we took was from a nice family biz named VIP Tours Cozumel .

Finally, I was able to dive deeper and omg it was so freeing to explore. I felt like a mermaid! 🧜‍♀️ Next step, learn how to hold my breath longer.

Did we truly relax and did it feel like a Minimoon? Well, we tried. 🙃 But when you’re running a business, you’re never off and you know what, I choose this life and I wouldn’t trade it for anything. I love what I do and I don’t need a vacation from it - I just need dedicated time to not forget that there’s more to life than the biz and I need to experience as much of it as I can with Sam before we can’t anymore.

♥️Cassey

Ps: For those wondering, we were in Isla Mujeres and then Tulum (which was major vibes) and then Cozumel which is where all of this go pro footage is from. The tour we took was from a nice family biz named VIP Tours Cozumel .

odeL0-1Jtg0.title: It’s not glamorous… but it’s real life #shorts #fitness #food #fitnessfood #protein
odeL0-1Jtg0.description:
Protein powder https://bit.ly/SculptandDebloatProtein

Ready for some realness? Sometimes I have NO TIME and I literally eat out of a Costco chicken can and pull leaves from a TJ’s butter lettuce bag with 3 min to spare between meetings.

It’s not glamorous and probably not at all what you’d expect of me, but it’s real life. I try my best to meal prep but sometimes you gotta go for the convenience!

Btw, those Supersculpt protein pancakes 🥞are AMAZE! I ate them nearly EVERYDAY on my 90 Day Journey! I prep the batter beforehand to save time.

2 scoops vegan protein powder
1 tbs tapioca powder
1/3 c liquid egg whites 
Pinch of baking powder
1 tbs water

This is 25g of protein (depending on what powder you use). Sometimes I double this and also add PB. LITERALLY YUM. 😋 

♥️Cassey

YZEJwHMI23M.title: I dunno why but this video makes me so emotional #shorts #fashiondesigner #fashion #fashiondesign
YZEJwHMI23M.description:
Ugh. This was supposed to be a trend. Not make me emotional. But my eyes are hurting from the tears I’m trying to push back in. 

This is my sketch book from 6th grade. I drew for fun when I wasnt doing homework, studying or playing tennis. I designed dresses for my Barbie’s, dance recitals, Halloween, and even my friend’s prom dress later on in high school. All I EVER wanted was to be a fashion designer.

My parents suppressed my dreams, in hopes of saving me from a risky career, but back then, it completely broke our relationship. I felt so lost, hollow, and purposeless. I had so much anger in my heart for them. 

I ended up sabotaging myself so I couldn’t take the MCAT, but still graduated with a degree in Biology, lived a short life in corporate fashion, took random Craigslist jobs, was an eBayer for a sec, taught Pilates on YouTube (while they were constantly asking “when are going back to school?”), and now…

*sigh*

I’m just so grateful. I can’t believe I’m getting to live little Cassey’s dream.

♥️Big Cassey
CEO + Head Designer of @POPFLEX and @blogilates

Fp79Cz7jtz4.title: So can we stop treating our bodies like fast fashion k thx #shorts #beauty #bodypositive
Fp79Cz7jtz4.description:
I saw a pic of Khloe Kardashian recently and boy does she look different. I mean, she looks incredible, but people are claiming she removed her butt implants! Which made me think…uh oh…it’s time for a shift in the female beauty standard 🙄

So, let’s revisit this experiment that I originally published in 2018: 

What I would look like if I had the “perfect body” throughout history.

2018-2020s:
Small waist, big butts, wide hips, thicc thighs, tiny waists, and full lips are in! There is a huge surge in plastic surgery for butt implants thanks to the rise of Instagram booty models. Even cosmetic surgery doctors have become IG-famous for reshaping women.

2010s:
All I remember is someone asking me for a thigh gap workout on Tumblr. I didn’t even know what that was. Then…the thigh gap became a full fledged obsession for girls all across the internet.

2000s:
Big boobs and flat stomachs are in. Breast augmentation is the highest performed cosmetic surgery in the United States in this era. 👙 It’s the age of the Victoria’s Secret Angel.

1990s:
THIN IS IN. Having angular bone structure, looking emaciated, and being super skinny is what’s dominating the runways and the magazine covers. Its called “heroin chic”.

1950s:
The hourglass shape is in. ⏳ Elizabeth Taylor‘s 36-21-36 measurements are the ideal. Marilyn Monroe’s soft voluptuousness is lusted after. Women are advertised weight gaining pills to fill themselves out. Playboy magazine and Barbie are created in this decade.

1920s:
Appearing boyish, androgynous and youthful, with minimal breasts, and a straight figure is in! Women are hiding their curves, and are doing so by binding their chests with strips of cloth to create that straight figure suitable for flapper dresses.

1400s-1700s:
The Italian Renaissance – Looking full with a rounded stomach, large hips, and an ample bosom is in. Being well fed is a sign of wealth and status. Only the poor are thin.

And here we are in 2022. Can we finally stop treating female bodies like fast fashion? It’s time.

♥️Cassey

3bLiZbpZ6V8.title: Was bored so I made a challenge. Wanna join? 30:300 Challenge, let’s go! #shorts #fitness #workout
3bLiZbpZ6V8.description:
I’ve been feeling really unmotivated lately. After my 90 day journey, I completely lost a sense of purpose, I lost all focus, wanted to rush through every workout or not even want to do them at all. My workouts didn’t feel meaningful and worst of all, it wasn’t fun anymore. 

Anyway, yesterday, I came up with an idea to switch things up and suddenly I felt that rush of excitement again!

It’s not that I don’t like working out, it’s just that I was getting bored and needed a change. So here’s the plan!

I’m doing the 30:300 Challenge.

🔲 30 min cardio
🔲 100 push-ups 
🔲 100 double leg lifts 
🔲 100 plie half deadlifts 

Note: I am breaking up the reps into sets and rotating through.

I am feeling like I need to take a break from all the heavy lifting and go back to my roots - more Pilates and bodyweight exercises. I’ll be doing this everyday for 30 days, and the reason why I wanted to go equipment free was because I wanted to be able to do this anywhere even when I’d be traveling.

I am EXTRA excited because Sam agreed to do part of the challenge with me. He committed to 30 min cardio and 100 push-ups everyday. So I guess he’s doing the 30:100 😄 We’re both filling out a chart everyday and keeping each other accountable. The motivation is BACKKKK and I’m so thrilled to feel that feeling again!

Anyway, this challenge was made first soley for me to get my motivation and focus back. Join in if you want, or not! Either way I’m on day 2 and feeling very sore. 

Comment below if you’re in! LETSSS GOOOOOOOO!!!

♥️Cassey

Q3Gvmnv707I.title: High protein cinnamon roll bites: perfect pre-workout & post-workout snack #shorts #recipe
Q3Gvmnv707I.description:
Grab a copy of Sculpt https://bit.ly/sculpt-cookbook | Get my protein powder https://bit.ly/Sculpt-and-Debloat

I love me a desserty no bake recipe that’s ready in 5 minutes!

I love making these a bunch of these ✨Cinnamon Roll Bites✨and then leaving them in the fridge so I can easily grab them for a quick pre or post workout snack!

Balls:

🔲 1 scoop Blogilates Sculpt + Debloat Sweet Cream protein powder 
🔲 1/2 c cashew, almond or sunflower nut butter 
🔲 3 TBS coconut flour
🔲 2 TBS monkfruit syrup (or any syrup)
🔲 1 tsp cinnamon 

Cinnamon sugar coat:
 
2 parts monkfruit sugar 
1 part cinnamon 

1 ball: 93 cals, 4g protein, 7g fat, 4g net carbs, 2g fiber

Makes 10 balls.

Recipe from my cookbook “Sculpt” which is finally back in stock and available on @POPFLEX  at popflexactive.com. You can get my protein at @Target  in store or online at target.com.

Enjoy!! Tell me what you think!

♥️Cassey

vUSLOLnlkbo.title: I designed the perf onesie for every torso length 🤸 popflexactive.com #shorts #fashion #fitness
vUSLOLnlkbo.description:
Shop the Corset Onesie: https://bit.ly/3QGyGoT

Torso length is what makes onesies scary.

Long torsos fear cameltoe.

Short torsos fear baggy crotch.

And then on top of that, the fear of looking like a giant baby. Trust me. I get it!

I wanted to toy around with the idea of constructing a keyhole at the midsection of a onesie to see if this would help with the various torso length issue. The goal was to have the keyhole adapt to the wearer: it would get bigger or smaller based on the wearer’s torso length, but would still be cute no matter what.

15 months from the moment this was sketched, the @POPFLEX  ✨Corset Onesie✨ is here! There were so many rounds of prototyping, but I’m happy we never gave up. It worked FINALLY, and IT IS A DREAM TO WEAR!

✨ the keyhole and adjustable straps help you find the perfect vertical fit
✨ the full body princess seams help lengthen your silhouette
✨ the v waist and fun regencycore inspired corset strings help create a snatched waist look

Also please remember that the sizing is limited because when I first designed this over a year ago onesies were experimental so I wanted to test in our most popular sizes first. Know that we have been working on plus size onesie development, but that it takes about a year or more for it to come into effect! So thank you for understanding and thank you for being patient with the process! I’m anxious to get them out too, but we cannot rush this.

Anyway, hope you love it! Would you give this onesie a try? I’m wearing XS.

♥️Cassey

EyJTSyFImes.title: 🍌+ 🥚🥚= 🥞 #shorts #recipe #cooking #breakfast #pancake #fitness
EyJTSyFImes.description:
Woooow would you look at that stack?! Yum.

You only need TWO ingredients for these babies: a banana and a couple eggs. That’s it! Then, all you have to do is mash ’em together and cook on a skillet on medium-high heat. Who knew a recipe existed that would totally satisfy any pancake craving without:

A ton of time (these seriously take like 5 min)
A ton of ingredients (like I said, only two!)

Oh, and these pancakes are FILLING. The eggs give you about 12 grams of protein and a little bit of fat to fill you up, while the banana provides some healthy carbs to boost your morning with a little energy. Here’s your new go-to breakfast…or snack….or lunch. If you’re like me, a pancake craving can hit any time of day.

KtI1zDGE9wA.title: It’s not really a video about bangs #lifelessons #shorts #motivation
KtI1zDGE9wA.description:
Grab my top: https://bit.ly/3xuKG4m

Several months ago I decided to buy some hair scissors off of Amazon because I just didn’t have time to go to see a hair stylist for trims. I mean I had already taught myself how to dye my hair at home during the pandemic so how hard could hair cutting be?

Apparently really hard.

I totally ruined my bangs and have just been trying grow them out. The unevenness has been getting worse and worse and today I just couldn’t take it anymore.

I took out those dreaded Amazon scissors again and decided I’d try once more. As risky as it was, I couldn’t stand NOT fixing the issue and remaining a victim of my own situation.

As I brushed out my bangs, I realized a huge life lesson.

All those times I tried to curl and blow dry and dyson airwrap and FORCE my bangs into place - it was all a waste.

No amount of superficial fixes was EVER going to solve the problem until I attacked the source of the issue.

Who knew my bangs would teach me a life lesson today.

♥️Cassey

Ps: top is the Allure crop from @POPFLEX

BoRB3rc4N64.title: Ok… that was v hard. (mat + onesie is from @popflex. bio link) #shorts #challenge #dojacat #split
BoRB3rc4N64.description:
Grab my onesie: https://bit.ly/3mRLVWd
Get on the waitlist for the CloudCushion: https://bit.ly/3xTUF4o

Omg I was actually really scared to do this because I injured my hamstring back in college when I went from a cartwheel dropped into a split direct onto hardwood floor at the end of a dance routine and heard a “pop”. 😳 The injury still restricts and affects my flexibility to this day.

Anywayyyyy for the Doja Splits challenge, with some slowwwww practice, pillows, and the Cloudcushion mat from @POPFLEX  (will be restocked soon), my hammies were saved this time!

I literally did this so many times this morning. Toppled over almost every single time too! It’s all in squeezing the thighs and core. Finally got it - sorta!

♥️Cassey

Ps: I’m wearing the Peekaboo Shortsie size small.

nzPF48z8otQ.title: Arms with booty bands? Yes. #ad #secretdeopartner
nzPF48z8otQ.description:
Arms with a booty band? Yes. Resistance training is a form of weight lifting! #ad #secretdeopartner I love it challenging my muscles in new ways!

Try this upper body routine:

Tricep press outs x 15 - light band
Bicep curls x 12 - light to medium band
Seated row x 15 - combine light and medium band
Triceps push-up x 12 - beginners can use the heavy band and as you get stronger, use a lighter band until you can do no band!

Btw I’m using the aluminum free @Secret Deodorant  with cardboard tube (appreciate the non plastic) in this video! I like the smell and how smooth it feels going on because of the skin conditioners in the formula. Try it if you’re looking for a new deo.

❤️Cassey

Yts20e4KGLc.title: I designed a regencycore-inspired #workout romper 💐 #shorts #fitness #activewear
Yts20e4KGLc.description:
Shop Neon Garden https://bit.ly/3Q6YHxl

I love rompers. When you don’t have to waste time matching your top to your shorts, getting naked on the toilet for a moment is no big deal 💁🏻‍♀️

Guys I’ve been wanting to make a workout romper for soooooooo long and I’m beyond excited to share with you the ✨Runsie✨ because it’s so friendly to wear!! I say that because I know onesies can be intimidating - showing every curve and bump - so it may not be your fave choice on a bloated day. But this POPFLEX Runsie you guys - OMG -  the floofy run shorts are so comfy and totally bloat friendly while the snatch panel cinches you in!

Best part is - if you need more support just pair it with the Refine Bra! I’m a 32A and wear XS so I don’t need a second layer for running or high impact workouts - but if you do, it totally matches! 

Btw - a note on sizing. This Runsie was designed in March 2021 and back then we were unsure if people would even like onesies. So we only made a limited range to experiment in our most popular sizes first. As you know product development takes a year or more, so even though now I KNOW we need to increase our size range to match our bras and bottoms (XS-3X) - product dev has begun but it’ll take a bit to appear on the website. The plus onesies will come but not for a while. I’m hoping to have the fit locked in by 2023! Earlier if we’re lucky! We’re still fit-testing. So thank you for understanding! 

Tell me what you think! Would you wear this?

♥️Cassey 

Ps: today is launch day of Neon Garden on @POPFLEX!

SHOP ⬇️
Collagen: https://bit.ly/blogilates-beauty-collagen
My cookbook: https://bit.ly/sculpt-protein-cookbook

I don’t drink coffee in the mornings but I do drink matcha lattes! The ones at Starbucks taste amazing but often have too much sugar and they make me break out. This version is filled with protein from the collagen which also helps with my hair growth and skin! Here’s the recipe from my cookbook, Sculpt:

💧1/2 c water
🥛 1/2 c almond milk (or any nondairy milk)
🍵 1 tsp matcha powder
✨1 scoop Blogilates Beauty Collagen (with Keratin) at @target
🥄1 TBS monkfruit sugar

You can totally add vanilla or cinnamon to this if you want to get fancy but I often don’t have time in the mornings so I skip. The one in the video is realistic for me and I make it daily! I love to warm it in the microwave for a 1:30. It’s so so perfect and adds slowness to my crazy mornings.

♥️Cassey

v_FTt-3Sn6s.title: It’s the #200ABCHALLENGE!! YOU IN!?? #shorts #abschallenge #fitnesschallenge #fitness #workout
v_FTt-3Sn6s.description:
Get my app: https://bit.ly/bodybyblogilates-app

It’s the #200ABCHALLENGE!! YOU IN!??

I want you to commit 200 reps a day for the next 20 days. That’s it. Think you can do it? 

100 reps of abs and 100 reps of heart pumping cardio to give you a perfect mix of strength building and fat burning!

Comment ✨YES✨ if you’re in! 

Now a moment for the Why’s behind this challenge:

1. I want you to find a routine you can stick to.

2. I want you to find the fun in being consistent.

3. This challenge will build your core strength with the ab exercises, and will also help you lean out with the cardio exercises.

4. It’s been a while since we’ve all done something together, and I felt like we needed a Summer Challenge to motivate us all again!

REAL TALK ON ABS: Seeing those coveted ab lines is due to a lower body fat % esp. in the midsection. Some people are genetically “gifted” with lower body fat and a higher metabolism and their abs will show faster than others, no matter they eat. Some people have to diet down hard and be in a caloric deficit to lower their body fat enough to see abs. And others may be working out really hard, eating very little, and still will hold onto fat because of hormonal things, stress, and medical history. So. I say all this so that you can understand that seeing abs is a different journey for every person! 

The ab exercises in this challenge will 100% make your abs stronger! The cardio will help you burn fat, but if you’re not seeing the results you want, pay attention to what you’re eating and do this challenge on top of your regular workout!

You can find the 200 ab challenge graphic in my app BODY By Blogilates and you can follow the challenge with videos in there for free! Link to download my app is in my bio.

Yay! Let’s all start Monday! You ready!?!?

♥️Cassey

LxnWSZDMVE8.description:
Grab my Shortsie: https://bit.ly/3x7xGl1

I didn’t even know it but as I was reviewing my footage I was like omg wait WHY ARE MY THIGHS SHAKING SO HARD!?!

Whenever your body does something it’s not used to, it’s a challenge for it! So yes, even though I’ve been weight lifting for a few months, doing heavy squats and hip thrusts etc, because I had not been doing elevated plie squats - my body was like wait hold on.

I’m a huge believer of cross training. That’s how you’ll build your strongest, most flexible, most balanced body.

RA6pyTgSGv8.title: Perception vs. Reality 💪 #shorts #fitness
RA6pyTgSGv8.description:
Perfection doesn’t exist. And I’m not just talking about self image. I’m talking about public perception too.

When my body became my billboard (as more eyes fell upon my YouTube channel), the narrative around it changed to match the story people wanted to tell.

A short timeline:

1. 2009: Started posting workout videos.

2. Early 2010s: “She’s too fat to be a trainer.”

3. Body positive movement.

4. “So inspirational that someone with a body like hers can be a trainer.”

5. 2019: Went on my 90 day journey to get in the best shape of my life - mentally and physically.

6. “She’s a bad role model. A complete hypocrite. She’s mentally disordered. A shame to all women!!!!”

7. Lost weight. Found myself.

8. 2020’s: “She’s looks so weak and skinny.”

I want to be clear that over the past 12 years, way more positive has happened than negative, but as a human, and an emotional one, it’s not easy to ignore what’s being said about me. So unfortunately, it takes up space in my brain and this timeline shows those moments that impacted me in that way.

Anyway, I’m always trying to work on not caring what people have to say because they don’t know my story, my journey, or my body. They have no right to strip me of my happiness or invalidate my strength.

So yeah… what you see isn’t always what you get… especially If you ain’t seeing clearly.

❤️Cassey

WsMNpcBIqp4.title: Design with me: how I turn ideas into ✨real✨ products #shorts #activewear #fitness
WsMNpcBIqp4.description:
https://www.popflexactive.com

I don’t believe in soulless products that are made cheap, bought cheap, and designed to be thrown away so you can buy more. Unfortunately, those companies (ahem Shein) are also dominating the market right now…😕 It’s reported that they made more than Zara AND H&M combined last year!

But I’m not here to compete (nor could I ever). I’m here to ✨create✨

To me, every single thing I make has to have a why, a purpose, and a meaningful journey into your hands. Every single style you see on the POPFLEX website takes 9-12 months EACH from sketch to being able to purchase because of how obsessive I get about fit and performance during the product development process. The fitting and prototyping is what takes the longest, but it has to, because if the garment doesn’t fit perfect or perform up to my standards, the whole thing is a waste of everyone’s time. Your time trying on something that doesn’t make you smile = my failure.

I don’t know what your perception of my company is, but the reality is, we’re a very very small team that works REALLY HARD and cares A LOT about you guys. We all read your comments. We have a slack channel dedicated to things you love and one for things you hate 🥲 The entire product dev team is women who work out! So trust me, WE GET IT. And just so you know, the word “cameltoe” comes up more times than you can even imagine in an average conversation 😅

Anyway, it was so hard to edit down 12 months into 60 seconds but I hope you can find some appreciation for the product development process. That’s why I get so excited when a design comes out because it’s like my baby! And look, I can’t tell you how other companies do things (though I CAN easily tell who takes time and who doesn’t based on fit alone), but I wanted to give you transparency into the @POPFLEX process.

♥️Cassey

Ps: For those wondering about fair labor with our manufacturing partners, fair is the bare minimum. We only partner with factories that get audited and can show us 3rd party certificates proving that they are socially and ethically compliant with labor, health, safety laws etc.

iKv5N1RBmP8.title: Omg this is so weird…anyone else??? #shorts #running #weirdfacts
iKv5N1RBmP8.description:
I wasn’t going to share (the pics disturb me) but thought that if anyone else out there has had mystery hives after a workout…then maybe this would be helpful.

I freaked out the first time it happened and I freaked out again today. The reason why it wasn’t as bad this time was because I ate 5 shrimp instead of 10 and stopped 20 min into my run instead of 30 min into it. Big props to Sam who told me to look at my food log from Jan 15. He somehow had a hunch it was the shrimp…

My body continues to surprise me. I guess I’m just going to skip out on shrimp entirely. If this is visibly happening after a run, what non-visible things are ACTUALLY happening under the surface? I don’t know but it doesn’t seem good.

I’m going to re-evaluate my diet and begin seriously logging again and paying closer attention to any reactions this week. I think my body has evolved and my diet needs to too.

Anyone else experience this? It’s super rare according to studies. I had never heard of it.

So weird…allergic to shrimp and running. Who would have thought???

♥️Cassey

kZFnAEIizsM.title: I did it. I designed the cutest workout onesie thanks to you 👏#shorts #design #fashion #fitness
kZFnAEIizsM.description:
Get the Peekaboo Onesie: https://bit.ly/POPFLEXonesies

Product design, to me, is problem solving. But to give it that @POPFLEX  twist, it has to be cute…or else it will NEVER EVER see the light of day!

Thanks for always leaving your comments - I read them, I write them down, and we talk about it in our product development meetings. 

I hope this onesie answers your wishes! Pockets and adjustable straps 🙂

I know some of you were asking for a more modest one with a closed back and longer sleeves. I’ve been trying to figure it out but to be 100% honest, I’m struggling! Once I come up with something I’ll get it into the prototyping phase…and then from there you probably won’t see it for 9-12 months. The product dev lifecycle is long because I care about every aspect of the design and I care that when you put it on your body thst you’re happy with the fit, that you ❤️ how you look, that you ❤️ how you FEEL, and that it PERFORMS! 

I am wearing the S in the Shortsie because they thighs grew so much from my 90 day journey and I’m wearing the XS in the long onesie version. 

Anyway! Let me know your thoughts on the peekaboo onesie!

♥️Cassey

rCiH6sTqon0.title: I love a good ✨voluminous✨ high ponytail 💁‍♀️

rShOQ-yqOM0.title: I can’t believe I get to check this off of my Dream List…
rShOQ-yqOM0.description:
I have a secret list of things I want to accomplish before I die.

I call it my Dream List.

I don’t announce or really share these as they are my deepest most unapologetic desires and I choose to work towards them silently, without anyone’s opinions distracting me from my goals.

But today…it’s time to share because one of the things on my Dream List is getting checked off!!! Honestly, I thought I was about 5-7 years away but, here we are, a little early.

When I got the call from @How I Built This Podcasts (my fave podcast everrrr) I DIED. I was SCREAMING.

I’ve been listening to @Guy Raz and his soothing voice since the beginning of time, learning from some of the most inspiring entrepreneurs in the world! It has ALWAYS been a dream of mine to be on his podcast. My goal was to do something so impactful that Guy would find my story worthy enough of sharing amongst his other incredible leaders and innovators.

Many of you know me from the free workout videos I’ve uploaded to YouTube over the past 13 years. But what you don’t know is that I spend about 95% of my day in product design, development and running the business. Yes, fitness will always be a part of my being, but entrepreneurship and creation is the thrill that keeps me wild with ideas. It is what keeps me problem solving and sketching and prototyping and testing! I LIVE for it.

I got the chance to talk to Guy about my backstory, where I am now, and my hopes for the future. I’m so not even close to where I want to be but I hope this interview inspires you to follow your passion - no matter if no one believes in you. You need to give yourself the 100% chance to succeed or else you’ll always live a life of “what if”? I’d rather try and fail hard than look back and wished I could have.

Have a listen to my episode and let me know the biggest lesson you learned. https://open.spotify.com/episode/3eCTr41e5tMbC9IUsyQd3i?si=lzQyIDoMRSuVabHBeYENhw

♥️Cassey

QaRe4HSLNoo.title: Having issues with your form? I got you 😉
QaRe4HSLNoo.description:
Having issues with your form? I got you 😉

I cannot stress enough the importance of FORM. Not only will you actually feel the exercise more in the targeted area but, you’ll also prevent yourself from being injured. 

When you’re hitting those floor ab workouts like leg lifts, pay attention to these signs: 

❌ Arch under your back
❌ Neck pulling
❌ Elbows cupping your head

Focus on these three things for the perfect form: 
✅ Head resting on your hands
✅ Shoulders lifted
✅ Lower back is pressing into your mat

9w3Rekjct-U.title: I designed the perfect zipper bra. 👋 sweaty, post-workout struggle 😅 #blogilates #shorts #design
9w3Rekjct-U.description:
Raise your ✋ if you understand the post-workout sweaty sports bra struggle.

Zipper bras have been around forever but I find them to be clunky and armor like. Soooo wanted to take a stab at making a dainty cute one with functionality.

All you need to know is that it’s got 3 HOOKS to ensure security! I saw this video on TikTok recently of a girl running on the treadmill and her zipper bra legit just slid down and the bra popped open! Omg!! Need to send her this!

I’m a 32A so I’m able to wear this for high impact workouts but if you’re above a B cup I’d say this is at most a medium impact bra. (We’re currently working on the ultimate crazy high impact @POPFLEX Active  bra - lots of testing - so please be patient if that is what you’re holding out for!)

The Don’t Sweat It Zip Bra comes in 3 colors (XS-3X): dark heather grey, black, and ivory. You can get it now here: https://bit.ly/dont-sweat-it-zip-bra

I hope you like! Let me know what you think and what other functionality you’re looking for in the perfect sports bra!

♥️Cassey

jhuTfGXcNm0.title: 2 Ingredient Nut Milk 🥛 #shorts
jhuTfGXcNm0.description:
Omg. I just learned how to make 30 sec almond milk and I AM FLOORED.

Not only is it cheaper than the store bought kind, but it tastes better and the best part - it only has 2 ingredients. You can alter how milky, fatty or sweet you want it too!

INGREDIENTS

🥜1-2 TBS of any nut butter (try to use one that is made of just nuts and salt)
💧4 C water

Then blend. That’s it! If you like it sweeter, which I do, add some monk fruit sugar to taste. Drink what you need then save the rest in the fridge! Not sure how long it saves just yet and I DEFINITELY will be doing this going forward! I am so happy!!!

What’s your fave non-milk milk? Let me know in the comments!

AG-3JrXhWGo.title: The Finale. #90dayjourney #blogilates #fitness
AG-3JrXhWGo.description:
The finale.

For those of you who read my last blog post, you know what a mental and emotional struggle I had the last 30 days. It was good to work through my feelings in writing, and I’m glad I had the privacy to be truly honest.

This video zooms out and looks at the entire journey. And you know what?

I am looking in the mirror right now, and I can honestly say, I AM SO PROUD of who I see in there. She is stronger than who she was 90 days ago: mentally, emotionally and physically.

I cherish this 90 day journey ESPECIALLY for helping me change my relationship with numbers. I was getting so messed up at the beginning seeing the scale go up everyday and had to rewire my brain to think: THIS IS OKAY. THIS IS GOOD. I eventually got to a point where the number didn’t control me anymore, and to me, that is the biggest win of all.

I feel so much gratitude right now. SO much.

A lot happened the past 90 (life stuff, work stuff, personal stuff…) but somehow my body and my mind managed to push through. I feel stronger. And that was the whole point. My Why.

Thank you for joining me on this 90 Day Journey. And thank you to everyone who supported me throughout. Your words really helped when things got too much for me to handle. Know that I read you comments and that they do make a difference.

♥️Cassey

Ps: Thank you to my friend Danny J for coming over to relive the bikini comp with me, but on our terms!!! She came to support me at my first (and only) comp ever, and at the time we only knew each other from online interactions. Now we’ve been friends for over 10 years! Had to redo the walk with her!

v2uRe4WN6AU.title: I designed the ✨perfect tee✨for me, and YOU. #shorts #fashion #design
v2uRe4WN6AU.description:
Tees. They have never looked good on me. So, I tried to create the ✨perfect tee✨ for me.

Finding the right tee is so hard because I want to be comfy and effortless but I still want to look feminine and stylish! Fitted ones look like they’re trying to hard and loose ones make me look like a man.

Sooooooo this is what I did:

1. Got a SUPER soft and stretchy fabric that DRAPED like a DREAM ☁️, so it could still be loose and comfy but would show my curves as I move!

2. Upgraded the shape to a loose fit with a CURVED HEM to make the box look less boxy and more romantic. Plus didn’t want it stomach-bearing, so I long-cropped it, making it easier to wear.

3. Added stylish details like a rolled cuff and a stitch down the back. Didn’t want to overdo a simple tee but could not bear releasing a super basic design! You know me. 😉 I needed quiet details. I needed something different, but subdued, so you could tell but couldn’t really tell.

I hope you like the @POPFLEX Active  Perfect Tee! I love how it looks on my body and hope you feel the same! Comes in 3 colors and there’s a whole bundle too if you want to save some money! ✨
Shop here ➡️ https://bit.ly/shop-perfect-tee

Enjoy!

b9i45GMzE4A.title: Let’s make the FLUFFIEST ✨protein pancakes✨ #shorts #food #recipe #protein #fitness
b9i45GMzE4A.description:
OMMMGGGG first of all, I cannot believe that I made it to day 90 of 90 of my journey!!! I’ll be DEXA-scanning, getting a spray tan, and finishing up my bikini soon for the final reveal.

Secondly, here are the protein pancakes I’ve been eating every day of my journey. I loved them so much that I actually did it want to go a day without eating them. They tasted like dessert to me. Speaking of dessert, after my bikini reveal, you better bet I will be going to indulge on some blue velvet cake with cream cheese frosting. 😋 Bloat and pimples are coming too but it’s worth it.

Okay!! Recipe for my Supersculpt Protein pancakes:

✔️2 scoops Sculpt + Debloat Protein Powder with Probiotics
✔️ 1/3 c liquid egg whites
✔️ 1 tbsp tapioca powder
✔️1/2 tsp baking powder
✔️ 1-2 tbsp water

Macros (no toppings): 182 cals, 25g protein, 0g fat, 14g carbs

More recipes like these in my new cookbook Sculpt which you can get here 👉 https://bit.ly/blogilatesnutrition

Enjoy!

PS: If you use a diff brand of protein, the recipe may not turn out quite right, as every powder is so diff in dryness, texture etc. I used Blogilates Sculpt + Debloat to develop the recipes in the book!

YYOiHdFosyA.title: This 90 day journey wants the most out of me. 🤪 #shorts #fitness
YYOiHdFosyA.description:
Wow. This 90 Day Journey just keeps wanting the most out of me. 🤪

My dream bikini turned out to be….a Malibu Barbie nightmare.

Look, there’s no denying that the garment itself is beautiful and is great quality, but sadly, it just isn’t me. It’s not my color and it’s not the right fit at all. I do not feel confident in it.

Unfortunately I cannot return it as it as custom made so it’s time to take matters into my own hands. I have to make my own bikini, so, welcoming all design and color suggestions in the comments!

Oh and for those who have no idea what’s happening or just joined the convo, I wanted to get myself my ultimate dream bikini for my faux stage walk at the end of my 90 days to celebrate 10 years since my first competition. No I’m not REALLY entering a bikini competition but I did want to treat it like I was.

Anyway, journeys are journeys! I must tweak and move on!

l_FYpRkWQYU.title: Funny that it’s the men who always say that. But have u tried? 🤔 #shorts
l_FYpRkWQYU.description:
Has this ever happened to you?

Honestly, I’m gonna call it what it is. It's been happening for way too long and continues to happen to me today. It’s misogyny in the fitness industry.

Just because I’m a female doing this exercise with control (which took years to build up to btw), “oh it must be easy”.

But if we saw a guy doing the same thing grunting and sweating, “oh it must be hard!”

I’m sick and tired of people (usually men) saying that Pilates “doesn’t work”.

LIKE OH MY GOD are you my body? Do you know my genetic makeup? Do you know my goals? How do you know what “works” means to me?

The truth is - there’s no one blanket answer for everyone’s individual bodies and goals. So don’t believe ANYONE that says there is!

When it comes to workouts, we should try them all so that our bodies stay well-conditioned, nimble, flexible & strong on ALL fronts. So if you decide to stick your nose up at one, you better bet your weakness is only getting weaker.

0e_7DMhsvOE.title: Behind the seams: How I designed the most ultra-flattering biker short 🧶 #shorts
0e_7DMhsvOE.description:
The Science of Fashion: Booty edition 🍑

Technical design - it’s what makes your clothes ACTUALLY fit and function! After the sketches, it’s the pattern making that takes the reins.

The tiniest shape differentiations can cause the biggest problems or be our biggest victories!

Today, we’re exploring the difference between the traditional J shape butt seam vs a straighter butt seam that’s featured in my new Cosmo biker short from @POPFLEX Active .

Because I have a smaller butt (and always will have thanks to genetics) I’ll forever be extra interested in finding ways to enhance the shape of my booty naturally!

Fun fact: you have no idea how much I hated taking booty thumbnails for my YouTube videos! I had to arch my back and stick out my butt so hard and STILL people would say “why don’t you have a butt??”

😡

Anyway!

The Cosmo biker shorts amaze me because of the way it hugs my cheeks… separately! 🍑 That’s what the straighter seam does! And no it is not uncomfortable, and does not feel like a wedgie at all. It’s because the thread stretches at the same rate as the fabric, so it does not hike up inside.

Anyway, if you’re like me and have a hard time shopping for bottoms that hug your butt instead of make it sag (I have the hardest time with bikini bottoms ugh!) then you might want to try these @POPFLEX Active  Cosmo shorts!


Ps: These also happen to be the comfiest shorts I’ve ever owned! The Airlite ButterSoft fabric is gummy and yummy! ☁️ 

Shop: https://bit.ly/CosmoBikerShort

craM4AbdgWs.description:
Here’s how to NOT QUIT. Save this 📥

It’s all about preparing for hard times. No one wants to think about failing. But actually you need to prepare for it, because it will happen, and you need to know how to pick yourself back up.

3 techniques to try:

1️⃣ If you feel unmotivated…
👉 Take a deep breath, count to 3, and JUST GO.

2️⃣ If you feel like giving up…
👉 Remember your “Why”.

3️⃣ If you feel like you’re not good enough…
👉 Think of 3 accomplishments you’re proud of and let it soak in.

Good luck!

True story.

I began working on Stardust back in 2019. It was supposed to be one of my most glamorous POPFLEX collections because the goal was to ring in the “roarin 2020s” with ultimate glitz!

We were almost done developing and about to head into production when COVID hit and the entire supply chain completely shut down.

Additionally, the glamour was not appropriate for the new 2020 climate, so I decided to end the project and stay in my sweats… while baking banana bread 🙂

Well…fast forward 2 years…I felt something itching inside. I felt like 2022 was ready for the glam.

So here we are!!! FINALLY. ✨stardust✨ has arrived!

What do you think? Are you into the sparkle? Do you want more? Or are you more into the basics?

vErqD0Q4n70.title: All bodies are NOT created equal and I took a DNA test to prove it.
vErqD0Q4n70.description:
I’m so sick of the toxicity and drama in the fitness industry. I hate that factions of people from certain camps of fitness will tear you apart and tell you you’re doing something wrong just because it’s not the way they would do things. #ad

WAKE UP.

We are all genetically made up of different DNA. So HOW can the same workout and diet work the same for different people?

When I saw that @circleDNA had tests to show fitness data about my body, I jumped on it. After doing my saliva swab, I waited a few weeks to get my DNA extracted and analyzed. The results confirmed a lot of things for me.

My optimal training type:

Low power - I’m not great at sprinting.
High endurance - That’s why I can keep pulsing and pulsing and pulsing…while talking and smiling!
Medium strength - Yes, so far this is true given the weights I’m lifting.

In terms of muscle development, it literally says:

“…your muscles are designed for repetitive work like high repetition weight training or longer duration cardio sessions…you will most likely achieve your best results when training with many reps, with slightly lighter weights.”

This makes so much sense!!!

Month 1 of my 90 day journey to muscle featured higher reps and not-so-heavy weights and I gained 6.3 lbs of lean tissue. In month 2 I switched to lower reps and heavier weights and only gained 2.7 lbs of lean tissue. There are other factors involved too but I think a big part of the difference was my training style.

Month 3 now features not-so-heavy weights and higher reps again. I’m feeling extra confident in my personal workout plan because now I KNOW I’m training optimally for my DNA.

If you’re interested in trying out @circledna make sure to use code “BLOGILATES” to get 33% off any 🧬 kit. BTW you can get over 500 reports across 20+ different categories and Circle DNA promises 99.9% analytical accuracy.

Https://www.circledna.com/Blogilates

♥️Cassey

Agree or disagree? Headphones in = don’t talk to me. 🙄🎧

Right??

Apparently gym bros don’t speak that universal language, so, like with all problems I encounter - I felt like it was MY DUTY to solve this once and for all!

It’s been 72 months of VIGOROUS research, development, testing, and patenting - but finally guys, IT IS READY!!!

Taking my love affair with unitards and my need to stay incognito at the gym, I present to you:

THE INCOGNITARD™

Honestly, I think it’s the greatest invention I’ve ever contributed to the world. I could die tomorrow knowing I accomplished the ONE THING I was put on this earth to do.

BLxk4q1bBwk.title: The science behind smelly armpits. #secretdeopartner
BLxk4q1bBwk.description:
#secretdeopartner

Never thought I’d be doing this, but I actually spent some time digging into the biomechanics behind why your armpits smell, and well, it is fascinating, so I had to make a whole video about it!

Where does the smell come from?

The stink happens when sweat reaches the surface of your skin and the bacteria in your armpits start growing and producing stinky gasses.

2 ways to prevent:

1️⃣  Traditional antiperspirants contain aluminum salts that mix with sweat, creating a gel-like substance that temporarily blocks pores, so it never has a chance to reach the bacteria, so → less smell.
2️⃣  Aluminum free deodorants like this one from @secret don’t contain aluminum salts. Instead, they create an unfriendly environment for the bacteria, making it hard for them to grow, so that when the sweat does reach the surface of your armpits, there is less bacteria producing gas, therefore → less smell. 
 
Interesting huh?

qrAOQgfSFu0.title: I tried to design the perfect legging… #shorts
qrAOQgfSFu0.description:
You can try these leggings at https://bit.ly/3GV1AfW

Things that annoy me about leggings:

1️⃣ When they give me cameltoe.
2️⃣ When they don’t have pockets.
3️⃣ When they pinch me.
4️⃣ When they make me look like a box.
5️⃣ When they’re see through.

Guys, I think I’m getting close. Like, REALLY CLOSE to creating the perfect pair with the latest version of the Popflex Active Utimate Hourglass Leggings. 

I mean…did you see what these pockets can hold!?!? I accidentally discovered that my leggings could hold my 40 Oz bottle the other night when I was walking upstairs holding 10,000 things and Sam was already asleep so there was no one to help! I actually shocked myself because it was never really the intention, but hey! I guess POPFLEX leggings can now hold tumblers and oversized water bottles! 😂

Any other features I should add!? Will you give it a try and tell me what you think? Always on a journey to improve and would love your feedback!

PqfwXy_czsc.title: This stretch will make you taller?!
PqfwXy_czsc.description:
If you're someone who works at a desk most of the day, spending all that time sitting down is likely affecting your posture! You may notice your shoulders rounding, or feel like your spine is compression.

I LOVE doing this stretch at least once a day to keep my spine straight & tall! I can seriously tell the difference - it looks like I've grown an inch! Obviously, it doesn't actually make you grow, but you'll look taller regardless.

dfb36oKKWt0.title: Exposing my body transformation (shocking before & after)
dfb36oKKWt0.description:
So, why did I make this video? 

I know it's easy to compare yourself to others' before & after pictures. These photos set expectations about how YOUR body could possibly look and even have the power to influence your diet & exercise routines. I wanted to show you how easy it is to be tricked by them.

With carefully chosen angles and clothing placement, you can literally take a convincing before & after photos within minutes of each other. So PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE be careful with who you trust, especially online! And remember, the best person to compare yourself to is who you were yesterday ❤️

rjIHE_4yHuU.description:

Adding in new movements will work new muscles (or the same ones in NEW ways) and ultimately get you stronger! Plus, let's be honest: it can be pretty boring to repeat the same few moves every day.

GFuhJQloXu8.title: 15 Minute Deep Stretch for Splits
GFuhJQloXu8.description:
My yoga blocks are from POPFLEX Active: https://www.popflexactive.com/collections/booty-bands

You know that feeling when your body needs a good, deep stretch?! That is totally me right now, so I hope you will come stretch it out with me!

We're gonna focus on those hamstrings, quads and hips to hopefully get into those splits! I'll be using yoga blocks to assist me, but you can do them without yoga blocks or with a item you do have, like pillows, instead.

1:33 Straddle
3:41 Butterfly

6:31 Half Splits - R
7:52 Low Lunge - L
8:42 Half Splits - L
10:10 Pike
13:32 Splits - R
16:46 Splits - L
20:51 Outro

oO9adFTPTk4.title: Here’s why it’s impossible to achieve the “perfect” body
oO9adFTPTk4.description:
It took me a long time to realize having the "perfect" body isn't actually attainable.

Hear me out - we can love and appreciate our bodies, and we can work on achieving fitness goals. But when it comes to fitting our current beauty standards, it's IMPOSSIBLE. Why? Because our bodies are treated like fast fashion. What's in one year might be out the next. 

I'm not gonna waste my time, energy and happiness trying to keep up. Our bodies are perfect because WE think they are.

#shorts

2vP-Yt2VDb0.title: Quiet Cardio 🤫  (apartment-friendly)
2vP-Yt2VDb0.description:
This is one of my fave no-jumping circuit workouts!! It's perfect for when it's too cold to go for a run 🙌  .

Do each move for 1 minute with a 15 second rest in between. After 4 rounds, you're done!!

Squat Touches x 1 min
Walking Lunges x 1 min
Side to Side Squats x 1 min
Plié Squats x 1 min

🎵 : Overwhelmed - Royal & the Serpent

Cassey Ho is an award-winning fitness instructor, entrepreneur and online personality. As the creator behind Blogilates, the #1 female fitness channel on YouTube, she’s transformed millions of lives through helping them achieve their strength and weight-loss goals. She focuses on making fitness fun and the results are evident. Cassey's unique format, POP Pilates©, which launched as a workout video on YouTube in 2009, has become a live fitness class that can be taken at gyms all over the world with over 3,000 POP Pilates classes being taught monthly. Her authenticity continues to shine through, making her one of the most relatable fitness icons online and beyond. She's also the author of the best-selling book, Hot Body Year Round and is the designer of her own activewear line, POPFLEX.

With a wide range of free workout videos available, Cassey's channel focuses on ab exercises, butt & thigh exercises, arm exercises, pilates, cardio routines, fat burning workouts, high intensity interval training workouts (HIIT), stretching and flexibility routines and so much more!


***

3qB-bqgFJK8.title: 15 min Ab Fit Test - can you get through it all?
3qB-bqgFJK8.description:
Whether you guys have been doing ab workouts with me for 5 weeks or 5 years, all your training has led up to THIS MOMENT. Can you pass the ultimate ab strength test??? I want you to go as HARD as you can and only take a break if you reallyyyyyy need it!

We'll do each move for 50 seconds with a 10 second rest in between!

00:00 Intro
1:48 Roll Ups
2:50 Single Straight Leg Stretch
3:49 Double Leg Stretch
4:49 Star Abs
5:50 Double Leg Lift
6:49 Single Leg Drop
7:51 Flutters
8:50 Windmill
9:51 Single Leg Jackknife
10:50 Cheerleader L
11:50 Butterfly Crunch
12:49 Butterfly Situp
13:50 Reverse Crunch
14:50 Corkscrew
15:49 Plank
17:09 Outro

ct9exVAd20I.title: Hot Girl Summer...Sculpt: Are you in?!
ct9exVAd20I.description:
ARE YOU IN?!? Sign up here: https://mailchi.mp/blogilates/hgss-challenge

We are reclaiming our summer back this year! You know what that means?! It means that summer sculpt is back & we're gonna make it a HOT GIRL SUMMER SCULPT!

Being a "hot girl" is so much more than looks... it's a state of being. A hot girl is unapologetically themself & is ready to show the world what they're made of! 

This transformation is going to be about so much more than just fitness. It’s going to be about rediscovering and growing your confidence, too! Because guess what? You are ALREADY a hot girl. It’s time to let her shine.

✨ 14-DAY HOT GIRL SUMMER SCULPT ✨ 

What is it? ➡️  A FREE 14-day workout program & meal plan designed to help you reach your physical and mental goals for summer! You will work out 30 minutes a day, use my registered dietitian-approved meal plan, and drink 64 oz water every day for 14 days.

When does it start? ➡️  May 3rd -16th. The first day is a brand new video so don't start without us 😉 

How long are the workouts? ➡️  Each day you'll be committing to 30 minutes of exercise!

Where can I sign up? ➡️  Sign up here to receive an exclusive PDF that includes the Hot Girl Summer Sculpt workout plan, meal plan & prep checklist: https://mailchi.mp/blogilates/hgss-challenge

Where can I find the workouts & meal plan? ➡️  When you sign up, you will be emailed an extensive PDF with your workout plan and meal plan! All videos will be available on my app, BODY By Blogilates or on youtube.com/blogilates!

_xNHoXHR9h8.description:

1fso0qOptxs.title: 10 Minute Fat Burning Cardio (no equipment)
1fso0qOptxs.description:
Cardio time! We are going to do high/low exercises to burn fat - we’ll start with the low intensity version then go to the high intensity version!

For example, we'll do 45 seconds of squats, and then move on to 45 seconds of squat jumps!!!!

Got it? Also, you can just do the lower-impact versions in place of the jumping moves, if that works best for you!

This is a 10 minute cardio workout- 45 seconds on, 15 seconds off!

RPLW0RvqmXw.title: What I Eat In A Day (photoshoot prep)
RPLW0RvqmXw.description:
90 Day Journal + Meal Plan Bundle: https://www.the90dayjourney.com/journey-packages

Since I have a BIG POPFLEX photoshoot coming up for our new collection (dropping March 23, 2021), I wanted to show you guys what I am eating to prep for my shoot. How I eat to prep for an event or shoot is different than how I normally eat (includes cakes, cookies, ice cream etc.) For photoshoot prep, I keep it gluten free, dairy free, and added sugar free + I drink 1 gallon of water a day. This is what keeps my skin clear, my tummy debloated and me overall feeling and looking my best. I know this (and know my body so well) because of all the detailed notes I took during my 90 Day Journey.

If you are interested in getting the recipes for some of the food I was eating in my video, you can find a bunch of it in my 90 Day Journey Meal Plan, which I wrote with my RD, Breanna Woods: https://www.the90dayjourney.com/

If you like my huge 64 fl oz water bottle, you can get that on: 
https://www.popflexactive.com/collections/water-bottles

If you end up embarking on your own 90 Day Journey, please document with photos and videos along the way! I will pick 5 people with transformations to feature in a YouTube video, and each will win a $250 POPFLEX gift card! You can me from anywhere in the world! I'll check in with you on the 1st day of summer!

HRH6dKo1EOA.title: 10 Minute Cardio Pilates Workout - burn fat + tone muscle, no jumping!
HRH6dKo1EOA.description:
For those of you who REALLY know me... you know I've always had a love-hate relationship with cardio. A long time ago, I actually used dread cardio workouts BUT recently, I've started to embrace them!!!!

So I'm actually SUPER excited for this low impact cardio workout! It combines cardio & pilates to burn fat and tone. No equipment needed!!

2:19 High Heels

3:27 Walk In Squat Pulses

7:53 Curtsy Lunges

eL8drCfjGLQ.title: 9 tips to start running when you hate it (realistic)
eL8drCfjGLQ.description:
Visit http://bose.life/blogilates to learn more about the Bose Sport Open Earbuds!

I used to HATE running. The thought of having to keep track of how many miles, or how fast I was going.... ugh NO. I've always preferred dance-like cardio workouts but I would do ANYTHING to avoid running, which even meant choosing burpees and HIIT workouts. Which says A LOT.

BUT one day, my sister invited me to go run with her. At first I was like "NOOOOOO you can't make me!!!" (seriously, I was that dramatic) but when I did it, I actually kinda liked it!! Now, I actually wake up almost every morning and get ready for a run to start the day!

If I can do it, so can you!!! If you've been looking for that motivation to start running, check out these 9 realistic ways you can start to LOVE running if you hate it!

Lq0xlybH4fk.description:
Today we are focusing on sculpting and shaping  your abs in your 21 Day Tone Challenge! We’ll work your upper abs, lower abs, transverse abdominals, obliques and TOTAL CORE. 

Plus to make it extra challenging, we’ll be using dumbbells! I'll be using 3-8 lb weights for today’s workout, the 21 minute Ab Tone, but if you don't have any you can do the moves without them - modifications will be provided for every exercise!

dBCcZH0nWMg.title: Your 2021 Challenge. You in?
dBCcZH0nWMg.description:
Here we go, you guys! 2021 is just around the corner and I want you to take on the 21 Day Tone Challenge...are you in? I am not going to get into what 2020 was...but personally I am glad that 2021 is just about here and I want to enter the new year with fresh, strong new energy!! Do you feel the same way? We may not know what next year is exactly going to look like, but I do know that we have some control over our destiny, so let's make the most of 2021!!

Get the Blogilates line at Target: https://bit.ly/3taUsGz

I wanted to make sure that with this program I created something that would give you structure, build your strength and make you happy. Isn't that what we all want? So here's how the challenge will work. For 21 days just follow the challenge calendar and be active each day for a maximum of 30 minutes. Simple right? We can do this you guys! Are you in? Let's go!!!

Here's what you need to do if you want to join the challenge:

1. Download the Body By Blogilates App here: https://bit.ly/bodybyblogilatesapp (free during the challenge)
2. Take a Before Picture
3. Complete the Workout of the Day
4. Drink at Least 64oz of Water a Day
5. Replace Refined Carbs with Vegetables
6. Replace Processed Sugary Foods with Fruit
7. Take an After Photo and Post Your Results

Click here for the printable #21DayTone Calendar: https://www.blogilates.com/ready-to-crush-the-21-day-tone-challenge/

Here we go, you guys! 2021 is just around the corner and I want you to take on the 21 Day Tone Challenge...are you in? I am not going to get into what 2020 was...but personally I am glad that 2021 is just about here and I want to enter the new year with fresh, strong new energy!! Do you feel the same way? We may not know what next year is exactly going to look like, but I do know that we have some control over our destiny, so let's make the most of 2021!!

Get the Blogilates line at Target: https://bit.ly/3taUsGz

I wanted to make sure that with this program I created something that would give you structure, build your strength and make you happy. Isn't that what we all want? So here's how the challenge will work. For 21 days just follow the challenge calendar and be active each day for a maximum of 30 minutes. Simple right? We can do this you guys! Are you in? Let's go!!!

Here's what you need to do if you want to join the challenge:

1. Download the Body By Blogilates App here: https://bit.ly/bodybyblogilatesapp (free during the challenge)
2. Take a Before Picture
3. Complete the Workout of the Day
4. Drink at Least 64oz of Water a Day
5. Replace Refined Carbs with Vegetables
6. Replace Processed Sugary Foods with Fruit
7. Take an After Photo and Post Your Results

Click here for the printable #21DayTone Calendar: https://www.blogilates.com/ready-to-crush-the-21-day-tone-challenge/

Here is where I get all of my music! Epidemic Sound: http://share.epidemicsound.com/sgFTn

#fitness #challenge #pilates

HRoUPr5QmN4.title: THE BIGGEST THING THAT HAS EVER HAPPENED TO ME
HRoUPr5QmN4.description:
GET THE BLOGILATES HOME GYM COLLECTION AT TARGET: https://bit.ly/3taUsGz

Exactly one year ago, I was sitting in a board room - heart racing, palms sweating, slightly delirious - waiting. Sam and I had just gotten off an international flight from Thailand, landed at LAX, and then boarded another flight to Minneapolis for one of the most important meetings of our lives.

I sat there nervously for the sporting goods buyer from one of the biggest retailers in the US to walk into the room and hopefully not hate the designs I was about to show him. I heard he was a REALLY tough one.

It seemed like forever that I was sitting there, waiting and waiting...but then, the door swung open. As soon as he walked in, I launched full force into presentation mode! I showed him how our vegan suede yoga mats got grippier as our hands got sweatier. I showed him how our fit journals have helped you guys achieve your goals! I felt like if I could JUST get him to not look down at his laptop for the duration of the presentation, then maybe I had a chance!

Afterwards, Sam and I weren't sure what to think. No purchase order was made. But he did ask a lot of questions. A good sign...right? We had no clue. This was only the second time in our life when we tried pitching a retailer. The first time was when we first started making yoga bags over 10 years ago, and that other retailer had totally passed on us. So we never really tried again, and instead put all our efforts into building our own ecommerce site.

The next day we flew back home, didn't tell anyone about our meeting, didn't get our hopes up, and just resumed normal life...until the definition of normal changed a few months later.

I remember the toilet paper shortages, the hand sanitizer price surges, and the whole world just coming to a halt. And in the midst of all...was when we got the call.

TARGET WAS GOING TO ORDER 13 OF MY DESIGNS AND STOCK ALL THE TARGETS IN THE US WITH BLOGILATES PRODUCTS.

UHHHHHHHHHHH. WHAT.

We went into full production mode and designed, sampled, tested, and WORKED LIKE CRAZY to pull this collection together for a December 27th launch. At times, it felt nearly impossible to achieve the quality I wanted, at an affordable Target price point, in the timeline we were given, with factory shutdowns and port delays. But...I seem to live a life that thrives off of challenges. Problems always push me to the brink of my creativity.

Well guys...I just went to Target and umm, I think it is safe for me to get excited now...right?

cuz...

OMG ARE YOU KIDDING ME!!!?????? HOW IS BLOGILATES - A YOUTUBE SCREEN NAME I CREATED IN 2009 - NOW A LITERAL ACTUAL BRAND WITH LITERAL ACTUAL PRODUCTS ON THE LITERAL ACTUAL SHELF OF MY LITERAL ACTUAL FAVORITE STORE!!??????????

Because of you.

I would have never been able to do ANY of this if you had never chosen to work out with me. If you had never chosen to trust me. If you had never chosen to evolve with me. Thank you so much POPsters. Thank you for believing in me. Thank you for changing the course of my life.

Love you,
Cassey

bt-bXFHGJqA.title: Extreme Weightless Arm Toner (30 min, no equipment)
bt-bXFHGJqA.description:
You guys when I say today's no-equipment arm workout is going to be INSANE... I'm not kidding. 😳 Your arms are going to LOVE it (and probably hate it a little too at some points) but you will feel SOOOO accomplished after!

We're gonna do 20 moves, 1:30 each. Your moves are:

00:00 Intro
2:14 Double Doors
3:48 Diamond Pull Downs
5:18 Tricep Kick 'N Dip - R
6:50 Double Angel Arms
8:24 Tricep Kick 'N Dip - L
9:50 Prayer Pulses
11:21 Half Cobra Push Up
12:51 Up Up Down Down
14:21 Walnut Crushers
15:50 Back Behinds
17:19 Oil Riggers - R
18:52 Golf Balls - Fwd
20:20 Oil Riggers - L
21:49 Golf Balls - Bwd
23:20 Single Arm Push - R
24:50 Single Arm Push - L
26:19 Palms Back Pulses
27:49 Robot Arms
29:19 Goal Post Punchers
30:50 Traveling Pushups

Try my level 2 arm workout: https://youtu.be/EEuFP9kLjNo
Try my level 1 arm workout: https://youtu.be/Y346900i9qE
